        "title": "Priority ranking (highest risk × lowest cost first)",
        "content": "1. **`store.py` dedup logic** — silent data-integrity bugs here corrupt the whole pipeline's notion of \"new.\"\n2. **`fetchers.py` parsers** — 17 bespoke parsers against undocumented/positional APIs (Google `ds:1`, Meta GraphQL, D.E. Shaw/Two Sigma HTML scraping) are exactly the kind of code that breaks silently on upstream layout changes; pure functions, cheap to test with recorded fixtures.\n3. **`filters.py`** — small surface, easy full coverage, protects against silently dropping/keeping wrong jobs.\n4. **`fetchers.py` retry/pagination** (`_request`, `fetch_workday`, `fetch_all`) — concurrency and backoff bugs are the hardest to catch by manual testing.\n5. **`notify.py`** — each notifier's env-var gate is a common place to introduce a typo that silently disables it.\n6. **`agent.py` db-new/db-mark** — watermark truncation-at-group-boundary logic is subtle and would fail silently (skipped jobs) if broken.\n\nNone of this can be verified end-to-end without also adding `pytest`/`pytest-asyncio`/`respx` as dev dependencies and a `tests/` package — currently there's no harness to run any of the above even if written.",
        "level": 3
